qas.question: Do any sees carry the right to the cardinalate?
Despite some traditions and rights, no see has the right to what?

plausible_answers.text: no see carries an actual right

qas.question: Which see carries a right to the cardinalate?

plausible_answers.text: not even if its bishop is a Patriarch

qas.question: Which bishop carries an actual right to the cardinalate?
Who is not sometimes entitled to at least one cardinal by concordate?
Who are not regularly made cardinals?

context: While the <b5_0>incumbents of some sees<b5_0/> are regularly made cardinals, and <b4_0>some countries<b4_0/> are entitled to at least one cardinal by concordate (usually earning its primate the cardinal's hat), <a0_0><b2_0>no<a0_0/> see carries an actual right<b2_0/> to <a1_0>the cardinalate<a1_0/>, <b3_0>not even if its bishop is a Patriarch<b3_0/>.
